br.usp.poli.takiyama.common
Class MultiplicationChecker

java.lang.Object
  br.usp.poli.takiyama.common.MultiplicationChecker
All Implemented Interfaces:
ParfactorVisitor
public final class MultiplicationChecker
extends java.lang.Object
implements ParfactorVisitor

Encapsulates the algorithm to check conditions for multiplication between Parfactors.

Currently, it supports StdParfactor and AggregationParfactor. If new types of parfactors are added, the interface needs to be remodeled.

Author:
Felipe Takiyama

Method Detail

visit

public void visit(StdParfactor p1,
                  StdParfactor p2)
Checks whether the specified StdParfactor can be multiplied by another StdParfactor. This is possible if all parameterized random variables f(...) ∈ Vi and f'(...) ∈ Vj such that ground(f(...)) : Ci = ground(f'(...)) : Cj, f(...) and f'(...) are identically parameterized by logical variables and the set of other logical variables present in parfactor gi is disjoint with the set of logical variables present in parfactor gj.

Specified by:
visit in interface ParfactorVisitor
Parameters:
p1 - The first parfactor to visit
p2 - The second parfactor to visit

visit

public void visit(AggregationParfactor agg,
                  StdParfactor std)
Checks whether the specified AggregationParfactor can be multiplied by the specified StdParfactor. This is possible if
  • They both have the same set of constraints
  • The specified standard parfactor has the same PRVs as the specified aggregation parfactor, excluding the child PRV.

    Specified by:
    visit in interface ParfactorVisitor
    Parameters:
    agg - The aggregation parfactor to visit
    std - The standard parfactor to visit
